		<h1 class="entry-title">As 10 States Cope With Measles Crisis Top Trump Official&#8217;s Anti-Vaxx Wife Issues Call to &#8216;Bring Back&#8217; Deadly Diseases</h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
		<div class="entry-featured  entry-thumbnail">

			<img width="940" height="490" src="https://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/darla-shine-s-4.jpg" class="attachment-patch-single-image size-patch-single-image wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="https://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/darla-shine-s-4.jpg 940w, https://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/darla-shine-s-4-300x156.jpg 300w, https://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/darla-shine-s-4-768x400.jpg 768w, https://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/darla-shine-s-4-640x334.jpg 640w" sizes="(max-width: 679px) 100vw, (max-width: 899px) 668px, (max-width: 1079px) 50vw, (max-width: 1259px) 620px, (max-width: 1449px) 66vw, 980px" />
		</div>

	
	<div class="entry-content">
	
		<div style='clear: both; height: 5px; margin-bottom: 25px;'>&nbsp;</div>
	
				
		<div class="proper-ad-unit">
    	<div id="proper-ad-ncrm_leaderboard"> <script> propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('ncrm_leaderboard'); }); </script> </div>
</div>

		<div style='clear: both; height: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px;'>&nbsp;</div>
	
		<!-- Go to www.addthis.com/dashboard to customize your tools --> 
		<div class="addthis_inline_share_toolbox"></div>
		
		<div style='clear: both; height: 5px; margin-bottom: 15px;'>&nbsp;</div>
	
		<!-- [0] -->Measles used to cause 2.6 million deaths each year. It was close to being eradicated thanks to the measles vaccine, which <a href="https://www.who.int/en/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/measles" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the World Health Organization reports</a> "prevented an estimated 21.1 million deaths" between 2000 to 2017. Globally, measles deaths had been reduced 80 percent, thanks to the vaccine.<p><!-- [1] --><p><!-- [2] -->Measles is "one of the world’s most contagious diseases." It is airborne, and causes fever up to 104 or 105 degrees.<p><!-- [3] --><div class='in_content_ad' id='in_content_ad_3'><div class='teadsNative'></div></div><p><!-- [4] -->"Serious complications are more common in children under the age of 5, or adults over the age of 30," the WHO reports. "The most serious complications include blindness, encephalitis (an infection that causes brain swelling), severe diarrhea and related dehydration, ear infections, or severe respiratory infections such as pneumonia."<p><!-- [5] --><p><!-- [6] -->People who have the virus can spread it for days before they show any symptoms.<p><!-- [7] --><p><!-- [8] -->Long-term effects include permanent hearing loss and intellectual disabilities, according to <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/measles/about/complications.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the CDC</a>. It can lead to pneumonia, which is "the most common cause of death from measles in young children."<p><!-- [9] --><div class='in_content_ad' id='in_content_ad_9'><div class='proper-ad-unit'><div id='proper-ad-ncrm_embedded_1'> <script> propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('ncrm_embedded_1'); }); </script> </div></div></div><p><!-- [10] -->And yet, despite all the evidence that the vaccine saves millions of lives, science-denying Americans are joining together for, as some news outlets falsely describe, the "right" to not vaccinate their children.<p><!-- [11] --><p><!-- [12] -->Fear and ignorance lead to movements like this, and they are propelled by willful stupidity.<p><!-- [13] --><div class='in_content_ad' id='in_content_ad_13'><div class='proper-ad-unit'><div id='proper-ad-ncrm_embedded_2'> <script> propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('ncrm_embedded_2'); }); </script> </div></div></div><p><!-- [14] -->Currently, there are measles outbreaks in ten states across America, entirely because parents are refusing to vaccinate their children.<p><!-- [15] --><p><!-- [16] -->"Last month, a public health emergency was declared in Washington State, where there are 53 confirmed cases of the highly contagious viral disease," <a href="https://kobi5.com/news/measles-cases-confirmed-in-10-states-95759/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NBC reports</a>. "The CDC says the majority of the patients were not vaccinated."<p><!-- [17] --><p><!-- [18] -->Among those spreading dangerous ignorance is <a href="https://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/?s=%22Darla+Shine%22" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Darla Shine</strong></a>, (photo, top, from her Twitter avatar,) who happens to be the spouse of a top Trump administration official. Former Fox News co-president <a href="https://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/?s=%22Bill+Shine%22" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Bill Shine</strong></a> is President Trump's Deputy Chief of Staff for Communications, also known as the White House Director of Communications.<p><!-- [19] --><p><!-- [20] -->Darla Shine gained notoriety last year when it was revealed that in the late 2000's <a href="https://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/2018/07/listen-top-trump-aides-wife-mocks-military-victims-of-sexual-harassment/">she mocked military victims of sexual harassment</a> when she hosted her own radio show.<p><!-- [21] --><p><!-- [22] -->Now Shine is getting more attention, thanks to remarks she made on social media advocating against vaccinating against "childhood diseases" including measles.<p><!-- [23] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [24] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Here we go LOL <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/measlesoutbreak?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#measlesoutbreak</a> on <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/CNN?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#CNN</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Fake?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Fake</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Hysteria?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Hysteria</a></p><p><!-- [25] -->The entire Baby Boom population alive today had the <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Measles?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Measles</a> as kids<p><!-- [26] -->Bring back our <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/ChildhoodDiseases?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#ChildhoodDiseases</a> they keep you healthy &amp; fight cancer<p><!-- [27] --><p><!-- [28] -->— Darla Shine (@DarlaShine) <a href="https://twitter.com/DarlaShine/status/1095679791154581506?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [29] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [30] --><p><!-- [31] -->Here are some of the responses her dangerous and false claims elicited:<p><!-- [32] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [33] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Child abuser.</p><p><!-- [34] -->— Eric Grant (@ericgrant) <a href="https://twitter.com/ericgrant/status/1095721967209070592?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [35] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [36] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [37] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Baby killer.</p><p><!-- [38] -->— Dr. but not the useful kind Susan Schorn (@SusanSchorn) <a href="https://twitter.com/SusanSchorn/status/1095718083535273984?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [39] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [40] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [41] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">I mean, it can only lead to permanent blindness and death. right?</p><p><!-- [42] -->Who WOULDN'T want their children to get sick and maybe die or be permanently injured to own the libs?<p><!-- [43] --><p><!-- [44] -->— Tim Peacock (@TimAPeacock) <a href="https://twitter.com/TimAPeacock/status/1095716416580476931?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [45] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [46] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [47] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">This is one of the worst tweets I've ever seen.</p><p><!-- [48] -->— Scott Tobias (@scott_tobias) <a href="https://twitter.com/scott_tobias/status/1095722541879054336?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [49] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [50] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [51] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Measles is a deadly disease that is preventable from a vaccine you idiot.</p><p><!-- [52] -->Stay away from people.<p><!-- [53] --><p><!-- [54] -->— Tony Posnanski (@tonyposnanski) <a href="https://twitter.com/tonyposnanski/status/1095718477757902848?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [55] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [56] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [57] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">And that’s why people used to die in childhood.</p><p><!-- [58] -->— Molly Jong-Fast (@MollyJongFast) <a href="https://twitter.com/MollyJongFast/status/1095717202433634305?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [59] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [60] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [61] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Ahhh yes, we all know how cancer is non-existent among baby boomers. You clown.</p><p><!-- [62] -->— Erick Fernandez (@ErickFernandez) <a href="https://twitter.com/ErickFernandez/status/1095696098738479107?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [63] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [64] --><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p><!-- [65] --><p dir="ltr" lang="en">I’m curious what your pediatrician thinks of your stupidity.</p><p><!-- [66] -->— Molly Jong-Fast (@MollyJongFast) <a href="https://twitter.com/MollyJongFast/status/1095726300516532229?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 13, 2019</a></blockquote><p><!-- [67] --><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p><!-- [68] --><p><!-- [69] -->&nbsp;
		
